The Kiss, Gustav Klimt

When I was a kid, I thought 'The Kiss' by Gustav Klimt on our wall was a portrait of my parents because I didn't know art. I saw it as a beautiful sign of family unity. I thought it was a portrait of them until my teens, when I discovered it was a world-famous masterwork

No ðŸ˜‚ , it was actually a remix of a Klimt's piece done by a Brazilian artist. But on my kid's mind, I had 100% sure the painting was about my parents, this connected me a lot to art. After a lot of years, I saw the original Klimt's piece on the internet and I catch it was a masterpiece
